A legislative aide to the Deputy Senate President, God’sTime Oghenebrorhien has tendered his resignation from the employ of Ovie Omo-Agege, the Senator representing Delta Central Senatorial District at the red chamber. The resignation is contained in a letter Oghenebrorhien signed and sent to Senator Ovie Omo-Agege through the head of Delta Office, Chunks Erhire at Urhobo House, in Ughelli North Local Government Area. The resignation reads in part, “I, Comrade God’sTime Oghenebrorhien humbly wish to inform you of my intention to resign my appointment as Legislative Aide with effect from the date of this letter. “My decision to resign became necessary after consultation with my immediate family, followers, political associates and leaders. I just want to move. “I want to us this medium to thank H.E. Senator Ovie Omo-Agege, Deputy President of the Senate for finding me worthy to serve under his office over the recent years”. Meanwhile, members of the ruling party in Delta State are celebrating the mass resignation of Senator Ovie Omo-Agege’s aides from his employ. For them, it is a sweet sail to victory in the forthcoming governorship election in the State.